This paper deals with a computational model that enables an agent to discover its kinematic structure from tactile information alone. The model is based on Bayesian nonparametrics and probabilistic modeling, which are common in the fields of robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves simulation experiments, which are typical in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper deals with motor coordination and the representation of body maps, which are relevant to the field of neural engineering (cs.NE).
